762
01:32:42,420 --> 01:32:44,440
Personally, I prefer something more
adventurous...

763
01:32:45,190 --> 01:32:46,380
...like wild life photography

764
01:32:46,760 --> 01:32:48,020
You like photography?

765
01:32:48,990 --> 01:32:53,360
Mum says the first word I said
wasn't Papa or Mama...

766
01:32:53,560 --> 01:32:54,390
It was camera!

767
01:32:58,670 --> 01:32:59,130
I'm Steve

768
01:33:00,200 --> 01:33:01,830
Steve? - Satyadev Mehta

769
01:33:04,610 --> 01:33:08,200
I've organized a car for you.
I'll get your trolley

770
01:33:10,680 --> 01:33:12,540
Okay Shalini, I'll take your leave.
Bye, Mahesh

771
01:33:14,350 --> 01:33:19,840
Here's my card. If you need
anything in Sydney, call me

772
01:33:46,780 --> 01:33:49,550
Well, I'd better leave now.
I'm sure you want to rest

773
01:33:49,890 --> 01:33:51,850
I'll send the driver to pick you
up tomorrow

774
01:34:15,440 --> 01:34:18,780
Yes, I'll tell Mr. Mehta

775
01:34:46,310 --> 01:34:48,800
Dad wants you to send him
a copy of the new contract

776
01:34:52,180 --> 01:34:53,510
You are coming to the meeting
tomorrow, aren't you?

777
01:34:54,880 --> 01:34:57,180
Can you give me our transaction
file?

778
01:34:57,450 --> 01:34:59,080
I'd like to know a little more about
them before the meeting

779
01:34:59,420 --> 01:35:00,890
I'll send you the file right away

780
01:35:06,760 --> 01:35:08,230
Is there a good restaurant around
here?

781
01:35:34,520 --> 01:35:36,550
Being alone in a new city
can be so boring

782
01:35:37,330 --> 01:35:38,590
But you aren't alone!

783
01:35:39,290 --> 01:35:40,490
Who said I was bored?

784
01:35:45,000 --> 01:35:46,930
Who'd have thought that
someday you

785
01:35:47,140 --> 01:35:49,000
and me would be sitting
here like friends

786
01:35:51,610 --> 01:35:52,630
Especially after all that happened...

787
01:35:55,780 --> 01:35:56,400
So how is Rohit?

788
01:35:57,950 --> 01:36:00,380
He's fine. I spoke to him
this morning

789
01:36:01,480 --> 01:36:05,040
I told him I met you on the flight
and...

790
01:36:08,590 --> 01:36:10,450
And he doesn't like you meeting
me! Right?

791
01:36:15,830 --> 01:36:17,700
But you're here.
Why?

792
01:36:17,900 --> 01:36:20,230
Akash, you don't know Rohit.

793
01:36:20,540 --> 01:36:22,700
He doesn't like me meeting
any boys

794
01:36:25,540 --> 01:36:26,770
But Rohit is a good guy

795
01:36:27,710 --> 01:36:32,580
He has a few faults but then,
don't we all. Me... you...

796
01:36:33,520 --> 01:36:35,510
Faults... and me!

797
01:36:38,120 --> 01:36:39,480
So tell me about yourself

798
01:36:41,060 --> 01:36:41,920
What do you want to know?

799
01:36:48,100 --> 01:36:51,190
Of course I have. But not for
more than 2 weeks

800
01:36:52,330 --> 01:36:54,530
Then there's another girlfriend...
another 2 weeks...

801
01:36:55,400 --> 01:36:56,200
And then another...

802
01:36:56,400 --> 01:37:00,340
stop! I understand how your
girlfriend system works

803
01:37:00,710 --> 01:37:02,540
What I don't understand is...
why?

804
01:37:03,910 --> 01:37:07,310
The fact is, I've seen many of my
friends with their "beloveds"

805
01:37:07,750 --> 01:37:10,110
They have everything but love
for each other

806
01:37:11,750 --> 01:37:13,240
That's why I think I am better off
as I am

807
01:37:13,520 --> 01:37:16,490
No questions... no answers

808
01:37:17,960 --> 01:37:20,690
I don't ask Rohit questions,
nor do I demand answers

809
01:37:20,900 --> 01:37:23,460
But he asks questions.
He demands answers

810
01:37:24,800 --> 01:37:27,130
I never said it's always
the girl's fault

811
01:37:27,840 --> 01:37:31,170
But relationships just get like that.
Start with joy and end in grief

812
01:37:32,240 --> 01:37:36,200
I see! So this is the result of
an end in grief

813
01:37:37,610 --> 01:37:39,380
Now I've understood your
2 weeks formula!

814
01:37:39,580 --> 01:37:40,710
No! It's nothing of the sort

815
01:37:41,450 --> 01:37:44,420
I have consciously decided not to
fall in love and ruin my life

816
01:37:45,950 --> 01:37:48,750
But love isn't about decisions.
It just happens

817
01:37:49,460 --> 01:37:50,420
Then I don't let it happen to me

818
01:37:51,630 --> 01:37:53,920
Give it some time. I'm sure
it will some day

819
01:37:56,460 --> 01:37:59,090
Why? Are you proposing?

820
01:38:08,640 --> 01:38:09,770
How was your day?

821
01:38:14,320 --> 01:38:15,110
Akash is nuts

822
01:38:38,910 --> 01:38:40,370
Turn it down guys.
It's my wife-to-be

823
01:38:43,240 --> 01:38:43,870
How are you?

824
01:38:44,580 --> 01:38:45,880
Hopefully a little less drunk

825
01:38:48,750 --> 01:38:50,720
Did you get my message?
Where were you?

826
01:38:51,750 --> 01:38:52,880
I met Akash for lunch

827
01:38:56,920 --> 01:39:00,380
I told you not to meet him!
Why don't you listen to me?

828
01:39:03,100 --> 01:39:04,890
Are you yelling at me in front
of your friends?

829
01:39:10,440 --> 01:39:13,900
I am coming there. It'll take some
time but I will be there

830
01:39:15,610 --> 01:39:17,910
As you wish, Rohit. Bye

831
01:39:24,550 --> 01:39:27,850
Pooja, I was in the neighbourhood
and I thought...

832
01:39:29,720 --> 01:39:32,020
Pooja, if you aren't doing
anything else...

833
01:39:34,900 --> 01:39:37,360
Pooja, I was in the neighbour...

834
01:39:39,230 --> 01:39:40,530
Bye mom, I'll call later

835
01:40:22,110 --> 01:40:23,410
Fine. And you?

836
01:40:26,780 --> 01:40:29,250
Subodh, this is Sameer.
Sameer, this is Subodh

837
01:40:40,460 --> 01:40:41,590
Are you waiting for someone?

838
01:40:42,300 --> 01:40:45,600
Yes. But it seems like
they won't show up now

839
01:40:52,870 --> 01:40:55,000
So tell me... what's the plan
after dinner?

840
01:40:56,050 --> 01:40:56,670
No plan

841
01:40:58,550 --> 01:40:59,670
Come on, let's do something

842
01:41:02,050 --> 01:41:02,680
What say, Subodh?

843
01:41:03,720 --> 01:41:05,520
I'm sorry. I've made it a habit
to sleep by 10

844
01:41:07,720 --> 01:41:09,520
One night won't change
your habit

845
01:41:10,230 --> 01:41:12,200
Come on, pal. Anyway,
it's Sunday tomorrow

846
01:41:12,560 --> 01:41:15,360
I know. Thing is I've to wake up at
5 and do Yoga

847
01:41:16,070 --> 01:41:19,040
Then some jogging and breakfast
at 8 sharp

848
01:41:20,400 --> 01:41:21,370
And since it's Sunday...

849
01:41:21,910 --> 01:41:23,700
...we spend the day at Kumar uncle's
beach house

850
01:41:27,010 --> 01:41:27,480
I'll be right back

851
01:41:33,720 --> 01:41:35,180
It's time for his bathroom break,
right?

852
01:41:35,890 --> 01:41:38,180
He isn't that bad

853
01:41:42,230 --> 01:41:43,520
So where are you off to?

854
01:41:44,230 --> 01:41:44,690
Let's see...

855
01:41:45,560 --> 01:41:49,690
If Time Table doesn't want to
come, may be you can join me

856
01:41:50,900 --> 01:41:51,870
I'm sure I can...

857
01:41:59,240 --> 01:42:00,540
If I call you sometime...

858
01:42:18,490 --> 01:42:20,960
Wow! What're we celebrating?

859
01:42:22,170 --> 01:42:22,790
You don't remember?

860
01:42:24,170 --> 01:42:27,970
It was on this day five months ago
that I told you what I felt for you

861
01:42:41,750 --> 01:42:43,380
To Subodh and Pooja!

862
01:42:49,590 --> 01:42:51,060
What's the situation like?
- Pretty intense

863
01:42:55,830 --> 01:42:56,460
Really, Mahesh

864
01:42:57,830 --> 01:43:01,790
There were such intense scenes
in the film! So moving...

865
01:43:03,340 --> 01:43:04,310
Please cut out the performance

866
01:43:04,670 --> 01:43:07,800
And forgive me for taking you
to see such a good film!

867
01:43:09,180 --> 01:43:10,300
You see! That's my biggest problem

868
01:43:11,180 --> 01:43:12,480
I can't bear watching good films

869
01:43:13,850 --> 01:43:17,480
Yes. You only like those
wham bang action films

870
01:43:18,020 --> 01:43:19,490
Anyway, that's all you can
understand...

871
01:43:20,020 --> 01:43:22,820
...because they don't require you
to use your brains or heart!

872
01:43:23,860 --> 01:43:25,660
You need plenty of brains for
these love stories

873
01:43:26,530 --> 01:43:29,160
She sits here shedding tears,
he sits there sighing...

874
01:43:30,370 --> 01:43:31,660
...what's all this lovey- dovey
stuff about anyway!

875
01:43:33,200 --> 01:43:34,000
You won't understand

876
01:43:35,870 --> 01:43:37,000
What're you doing man, let's go

877
01:43:56,730 --> 01:44:00,030
Wonder why
people fall in love

878
01:44:04,400 --> 01:44:07,700
Wonder why people
are ready to die for someone

879
01:44:11,910 --> 01:44:15,210
Wonder why
people fall in love

880
01:44:15,750 --> 01:44:19,040
Wonder why people
are ready to die for someone

881
01:44:19,750 --> 01:44:23,710
Wonder why,
Oh wonder why...

882
01:44:27,420 --> 01:44:30,880
Wonder why... why... why!

883
01:44:35,600 --> 01:44:39,230
Just think about it,
there is only grief in love

884
01:44:40,600 --> 01:44:44,230
As for love's cruelty,
it's past counting

885
01:44:45,610 --> 01:44:49,740
When in love
your head must remain bowed

886
01:44:50,780 --> 01:44:54,910
Even when in pain
you have to smile

887
01:44:55,120 --> 01:44:58,250
Why fill your own life
with poison?

888
01:45:02,630 --> 01:45:05,920
Wonder why
people fall in love

889
01:45:07,960 --> 01:45:11,420
Wonder why,
Oh wonder why

890
01:45:12,970 --> 01:45:16,600
Wonder why why... why...

891
01:45:21,640 --> 01:45:27,780
Without love
what's left in life

892
01:45:29,150 --> 01:45:35,950
Without love
A person is Ionely

893
01:45:40,500 --> 01:45:43,800
Without love
what's there in life

894
01:45:44,330 --> 01:45:47,460
Without love
A person is Ionely

895
01:45:48,170 --> 01:45:51,300
Love brings colour
into your life

896
01:45:51,840 --> 01:45:55,140
Love brings beauty
into your life

897
01:45:55,680 --> 01:45:58,980
People fall in love
but hide it

898
01:46:03,190 --> 01:46:06,480
Wonder why they fear
expressing it openly

899
01:46:08,520 --> 01:46:11,980
Wonder why,
Oh wonder why...

900
01:46:13,360 --> 01:46:16,990
Wonder why why why!

901
01:47:04,910 --> 01:47:07,540
Love is just
needless trouble

902
01:47:09,750 --> 01:47:12,720
Love is beautiful
in every aspect

903
01:47:14,260 --> 01:47:17,710
We are all better off
far away from love

904
01:47:19,600 --> 01:47:22,720
Love's every form
is the assured truth

905
01:47:23,100 --> 01:47:27,400
He that tests love's
waters...

906
01:47:28,100 --> 01:47:31,230
...neither drowns nor floats

907
01:47:31,940 --> 01:47:34,240
Wonder why?

908
01:47:34,440 --> 01:47:37,570
Everyone but everyone
falls in love

909
01:47:37,950 --> 01:47:41,750
Wonder why only you
keep avoiding it

910
01:47:41,950 --> 01:47:45,750
Wonder why...

911
01:47:45,960 --> 01:47:48,080
Wonder why...

912
01:47:49,630 --> 01:47:53,580
Wonder why why why!

913
01:48:27,530 --> 01:48:28,330
Tell me something Shalini

914
01:48:29,360 --> 01:48:30,830
Why're you so scared of
sitting on these rides?

915
01:48:31,700 --> 01:48:32,500
I m not scared

916
01:48:33,870 --> 01:48:38,500
I think only those who aren't right
in their heads enjoy these rides

917
01:48:41,210 --> 01:48:41,840
Interesting excuse

918
01:48:42,710 --> 01:48:44,840
You need courage to sit on
these rides! You need guts

919
01:48:46,050 --> 01:48:48,350
But don't worry. There are many
cowards like you around here

920
01:48:49,550 --> 01:48:50,850
Look. There's one right there

921
01:48:55,720 --> 01:48:56,690
It's not like that at all

922
01:48:57,390 --> 01:49:01,520
If it isn't like that, then get on
that ride with me

923
01:49:06,570 --> 01:49:07,700
Why? No guts?

924
01:49:09,740 --> 01:49:10,360
It's getting late

925
01:49:16,250 --> 01:49:17,710
I'm going on that ride

926
01:49:18,420 --> 01:49:21,720
If you want, you can come with me.
Or sit here and get bored

927
01:49:28,160 --> 01:49:30,790
Absolutely no guts

928
01:50:29,950 --> 01:50:31,920
Hurry. We can catch this train

929
01:52:51,600 --> 01:52:53,720
Really Shalini! How could you
scare that poor old man!

930
01:53:08,980 --> 01:53:10,110
How did it go?

931
01:53:10,980 --> 01:53:13,610
Really well. They like my work

932
01:53:13,990 --> 01:53:17,440
And... they want me to
come back

933
01:53:18,490 --> 01:53:19,460
That's great

934
01:53:20,330 --> 01:53:21,290
When will you have to go?

935
01:53:21,990 --> 01:53:24,290
I've just returned and you're
asking about my leaving

936
01:53:27,170 --> 01:53:28,460
Did you talk to Sameer?

937
01:53:28,830 --> 01:53:29,460
No. Why?

938
01:53:30,170 --> 01:53:33,140
He came over the morning
you left

939
01:53:33,500 --> 01:53:34,800
He seemed very troubled

940
01:53:36,840 --> 01:53:39,810
What did he say?
- Nothing

941
01:53:49,350 --> 01:53:51,820
When did you get back?

942
01:53:55,360 --> 01:53:56,990
How are you? How's everything?

943
01:53:57,200 --> 01:53:58,660
Great. How are things with you
man?

944
01:53:59,030 --> 01:54:00,660
It's a very long story

945
01:54:01,030 --> 01:54:02,160
Let's go up and talk

946
01:54:07,000 --> 01:54:09,470
Okay, so here's the situation

947
01:54:10,840 --> 01:54:12,970
You are pretty good friends.
Hang out together

948
01:54:13,680 --> 01:54:15,140
But you still haven't told her
how you feel

949
01:54:16,850 --> 01:54:17,970
I've tried very hard...

950
01:54:21,350 --> 01:54:22,650
But the words just don't come out

951
01:54:26,860 --> 01:54:27,980
Didn't she have a boyfriend?

952
01:54:30,030 --> 01:54:31,650
Yup. She did... but not anymore

953
01:54:32,860 --> 01:54:34,660
I don't know what Pooja saw
in him

954
01:54:35,200 --> 01:54:37,670
I mean he was sweet
but what a bore!

955
01:54:40,200 --> 01:54:43,170
One day I made the mistake of
going for a drive with them

956
01:54:45,240 --> 01:54:46,210
See this place...

957
01:54:46,910 --> 01:54:49,540
I met Pooja for the first time
on 15th September right here

958
01:54:52,750 --> 01:54:56,210
Exactly 7 days later, we came here
to have ice cream... 22nd September

959
01:54:59,920 --> 01:55:01,220
You wouldn't remember the time,
would you?

960
01:55:01,760 --> 01:55:05,060
Of course I remember.
It was exactly 5.55

961
01:55:11,940 --> 01:55:14,230
That's not all

962
01:55:15,110 --> 01:55:18,230
He'd buy her a balloon
everyday

963
01:55:18,610 --> 01:55:19,230
Balloon...?

964
01:55:20,280 --> 01:55:24,740
Yes. You know those heart shaped
ones you get at signals

965
01:55:28,290 --> 01:55:30,750
It's okay but...
Everyday!

966
01:55:31,120 --> 01:55:31,920
One balloon a day!

967
01:55:37,430 --> 01:55:39,400
I knew the guy was deranged

968
01:55:49,610 --> 01:55:53,240
If you love Pooja so much,
why haven't you told her?

969
01:55:55,780 --> 01:55:56,910
I was afraid...

970
01:55:58,780 --> 01:56:01,750
What if Pooja says no?

971
01:56:03,620 --> 01:56:06,750
I'd even lose this friendship
we share now...

972
01:56:07,630 --> 01:56:08,590
and be all alone

973
01:56:13,630 --> 01:56:16,430
You weren't here.
Nor was Akash

974
01:56:22,970 --> 01:56:23,940
Anyway, you're here now

975
01:56:24,810 --> 01:56:26,780
And I feel stronger knowing
that you're here for me

976
01:56:28,150 --> 01:56:29,440
I'm always here for you, Sameer

977
01:56:33,480 --> 01:56:34,280
Then... shall I tell her today?

978
01:56:37,160 --> 01:56:37,780
Tell her

979
01:56:41,490 --> 01:56:43,620
Pooja, there's something
I need to tell you

980
01:56:46,660 --> 01:56:51,290
I wonder what if the arranging
incident hadn't happened

981
01:56:54,010 --> 01:56:56,800
If we hadn't met the way we
did...

982
01:56:57,680 --> 01:57:00,970
If I had met you somewhere else,
would we be the same as we are now?

983
01:57:01,680 --> 01:57:04,650
And if we weren't the way we are,
how else would we be?

984
01:57:05,020 --> 01:57:06,480
If you thought differently
about me...

985
01:57:06,680 --> 01:57:08,810
...if I thought differently about
you, what'd happen?

986
01:57:10,920 --> 01:57:14,550
What's happening now?
...What am I saying?

987
01:57:16,430 --> 01:57:21,730
Just a lot of ifs!
What's the matter?

988
01:57:24,770 --> 01:57:25,900
The matter is just that...

989
01:57:28,110 --> 01:57:29,230
I'm falling in love with you

990
01:57:31,950 --> 01:57:34,240
I agree that we don't know
each other very well

991
01:57:41,290 --> 01:57:45,420
If you trust me at all, believe
that I am telling the truth

992
01:58:29,100 --> 01:58:34,060
I look everywhere for her.
But I still haven't found her

993
01:58:34,270 --> 01:58:39,580
Where is the girl
in whose love I can believe?

994
01:58:44,450 --> 01:58:46,750
She who loves only me

995
01:58:46,950 --> 01:58:49,250
She must be even ready
to say...

996
01:58:49,460 --> 01:58:51,750
"O listen, you are the one
who has my heart"

997
01:58:51,960 --> 01:58:54,760
Oh, where is that girl?

998
01:59:04,470 --> 01:59:09,430
She who lives in your dream
as love's beautiful embodiment...

999
01:59:09,640 --> 01:59:11,940
You will find her someday
or other

1000
01:59:12,150 --> 01:59:15,110
Just look here and there

1001
01:59:19,820 --> 01:59:22,120
Let's both go and find her...

1002
01:59:22,320 --> 01:59:24,620
This angel, this fairy,
this damsel so dainty...

1003
01:59:24,830 --> 01:59:27,120
...who upon seeing,
you will say

1004
01:59:27,330 --> 01:59:30,130
She is right here!

1005
02:00:05,530 --> 02:00:09,160
I wonder why
I had this thought...

1006
02:00:09,870 --> 02:00:15,500
Could you be the
dream girl?

1007
02:00:15,710 --> 02:00:25,180
You have all the graces
that I search for everywhere

1008
02:00:25,390 --> 02:00:27,850
I think you are deluded

1009
02:00:28,050 --> 02:00:30,350
I wonder what you think I am

1010
02:00:30,560 --> 02:00:32,860
I am no angel or fairy
nor any celestial nymph

1011
02:00:33,060 --> 02:00:36,030
Don't have any such
illusions

1012
02:00:40,730 --> 02:00:45,540
I look everywhere for her.
But I still haven't found her

1013
02:00:45,740 --> 02:00:51,040
Where is the girl
in whose love I can believe?

1014
02:01:26,450 --> 02:01:30,410
Suppose I say to you...

1015
02:01:30,620 --> 02:01:36,420
All I think of
is you and only you

1016
02:01:36,620 --> 02:01:40,580
You must know
this is what I desire...

1017
02:01:40,790 --> 02:01:46,260
...you must be with me,
only with me

1018
02:01:46,470 --> 02:01:48,760
Oh, what have you made me believe!

1019
02:01:48,970 --> 02:01:51,270
Oh, how you make my heart beat!

1020
02:01:51,470 --> 02:01:53,770
You melt my body and soul...

1021
02:01:53,970 --> 02:01:56,770
...reciting this saga of yours

1022
02:02:06,650 --> 02:02:11,450
I look everywhere for her.
But I still haven't found her

1023
02:02:11,660 --> 02:02:14,460
Where is the girl
in whose love I can believe?

1024
02:02:14,660 --> 02:02:19,120
Oh, where is that girl?
That girl is here!

1025
02:02:19,330 --> 02:02:35,310
Where is that girl?
- That girl is here!

1026
02:03:03,040 --> 02:03:06,010
I can't believe that it's already
time for you to leave

1027
02:03:08,050 --> 02:03:10,020
Don't worry, Mom.
I'll be back soon

1028
02:03:10,550 --> 02:03:12,020
Three months is not soon

1029
02:03:13,550 --> 02:03:14,680
And that's this time

1030
02:03:16,560 --> 02:03:18,520
You don't know how long
you'll be gone next time

1031
02:03:21,560 --> 02:03:25,860
Siddharth... have you thought about
marriage?

1032
02:03:26,070 --> 02:03:26,690
Mom!

1033
02:03:28,570 --> 02:03:29,540
What Mom!

1034
02:03:32,070 --> 02:03:35,370
Some other time, okay?
- But why? Why not now?

1035
02:03:39,250 --> 02:03:43,880
It's just... forget it, Mom.
You won't understand

1036
02:03:46,590 --> 02:03:49,710
I'm your mother! If I can't
understand you, who else will?

1037
02:03:52,760 --> 02:03:53,880
Is there someone you like?

1038
02:03:59,270 --> 02:04:01,230
Sid, what's the matter?

1039
02:04:02,270 --> 02:04:03,900
You've never hidden anything
from me

1040
02:04:04,100 --> 02:04:06,570
Yes, Ma. But there are some things
that you just can't tell somebody

1041
02:04:06,940 --> 02:04:08,070
Yes there are...

1042
02:04:08,780 --> 02:04:12,070
But I can see there's something
eating away at you inside

1043
02:04:12,450 --> 02:04:14,570
Will you keep it bottled up inside
all your life?

1044
02:04:21,950 --> 02:04:23,580
Ma, I'm telling you
you won't understand!

1045
02:04:24,460 --> 02:04:25,580
Why won't I understand?

1046
02:04:26,960 --> 02:04:28,430
Try telling me

1047
02:04:32,130 --> 02:04:34,760
What is this thing that I don't
have the right to know?

1048
02:04:39,140 --> 02:04:39,760
What's the matter?

1049
02:04:52,150 --> 02:04:53,120
That Tara Jaiswal?

1050
02:04:55,890 --> 02:04:58,020
I've met her so many times...
But... she...

1051
02:05:00,730 --> 02:05:01,850
When did this start?

1052
02:05:03,060 --> 02:05:04,530
I don't know when...

1053
02:05:06,570 --> 02:05:08,190
I won't let you ruin your life!

1054
02:05:09,070 --> 02:05:11,200
Have you any inkling of what
you are saying?

1055
02:05:12,410 --> 02:05:14,370
My son has fallen in love with
a woman who...

1056
02:05:15,070 --> 02:05:16,700
You were right I wouldn't
understand

1057
02:05:18,240 --> 02:05:20,870
And what has she told you,
that she loves you?

1058
02:05:21,250 --> 02:05:23,880
She must've seduced you with her
sad stories

1059
02:05:24,520 --> 02:05:25,640
What did she say to you?
- She said nothing!

1060
02:05:32,190 --> 02:05:33,160
She doesn't even know that I...

1061
02:05:42,540 --> 02:05:44,330
Your mother is absolutely right,
Siddharth

1062
02:05:45,370 --> 02:05:50,330
Don't ruin your life over me. And the
little peace I have left in my life...

1063
02:05:51,210 --> 02:05:53,340
Please don't take it away
from me

1064
02:06:13,470 --> 02:06:16,440
Go away! - Please listen to me

1065
02:06:16,640 --> 02:06:17,610
I don't want to hear anything

1066
02:06:18,640 --> 02:06:21,940
Have I ever made you feel
that I love you...

1067
02:06:22,140 --> 02:06:23,770
...or want a relationship
with you?

1068
02:06:25,480 --> 02:06:25,950
No

1069
02:06:26,650 --> 02:06:28,120
Then what made you think...

1070
02:06:28,650 --> 02:06:29,780
...that you and I could...

1071
02:06:30,320 --> 02:06:31,620
...have any such relationship?

1072
02:06:35,490 --> 02:06:37,120
This is the problem with your
generation

1073
02:06:38,160 --> 02:06:43,290
You all think anything goes.
But that's not so, Siddharth

1074
02:06:46,500 --> 02:06:48,300
Why just me?

1075
02:06:49,170 --> 02:06:50,470
You have also caused your mother
a lot of pain

1076
02:06:53,010 --> 02:06:53,800
Please sit down

1077
02:07:24,040 --> 02:07:27,340
I'm so sorry that I caused you
and my mother such pain

1078
02:07:31,380 --> 02:07:33,680
I'm sorry you had to hear
all this because of me

1079
02:07:37,220 --> 02:07:39,190
But it's true that I love you

1080
02:07:53,030 --> 02:07:56,330
It's also true that I never
wanted you to know it

1081
02:07:58,510 --> 02:07:59,970
Because I knew that you...

1082
02:08:02,010 --> 02:08:02,810
...would never be able to understand

1083
02:08:08,250 --> 02:08:09,720
I just want to see you happy

1084
02:08:14,590 --> 02:08:19,550
And if knowing the truth
has caused you pain today...

1085
02:08:22,260 --> 02:08:25,560
All I can say is, that wasn't
my intention

1086
02:08:37,950 --> 02:08:41,070
Sid, please leave now

1087
02:09:15,580 --> 02:09:16,380
After the workshop...

1088
02:09:19,090 --> 02:09:21,560
I think I'll go stay at uncle's
farm house for a while

1089
02:09:23,760 --> 02:09:25,230
It's a good place to paint

1090
02:09:35,600 --> 02:09:36,730
Will you come with me?

1091
02:09:40,780 --> 02:09:42,240
I don't want to go without you

1092
02:10:20,820 --> 02:10:21,440
Just a minute...

1093
02:11:17,910 --> 02:11:18,870
You look very lovely

1094
02:11:24,580 --> 02:11:26,880
So, why are we here?

1095
02:11:28,250 --> 02:11:32,050
To prove to you that a thing called
love does exist in this world

1096
02:11:35,260 --> 02:11:36,550
Don't you ever give up?

1097
02:11:37,760 --> 02:11:39,390
Shut up and lets go in

1098
02:12:07,460 --> 02:12:09,750
Why are we here?
- To watch an opera

1099
02:12:11,130 --> 02:12:11,920
Yes, but why?

1100
02:12:13,290 --> 02:12:14,760
You'll know when the time comes

1101
02:13:22,200 --> 02:13:24,490
The girl's name is Cressida
and the boy is Troilus

1102
02:13:26,030 --> 02:13:27,830
They love each other very much

1103
02:13:47,060 --> 02:13:48,520
But Troilus must go now

1104
02:13:49,890 --> 02:13:51,860
He has to go to war for his country

1105
02:13:53,730 --> 02:13:56,200
Cressida is afraid something may
happen to him

1106
02:13:58,400 --> 02:14:00,530
Troilus is telling her
nothing will happen to him

1107
02:15:21,820 --> 02:15:27,450
This is the spirit of Troilus...
standing at heaven's gate

1108
02:15:29,160 --> 02:15:30,630
But he doesn't want to go inside

1109
02:15:33,330 --> 02:15:35,130
He is asking God for one day

1110
02:15:37,670 --> 02:15:39,460
He wants to meet Cressida for
one last time

1111
02:15:41,510 --> 02:15:44,800
And tell her how much he loves her

1112
02:15:48,180 --> 02:15:49,810
If he is given one day...

1113
02:15:51,350 --> 02:15:53,480
He is willing to die a thousand
deaths

1114
02:16:01,530 --> 02:16:03,150
Shut your eyes, Akash

1115
02:16:09,200 --> 02:16:09,670
Think...

1116
02:16:11,200 --> 02:16:11,670
Who is it...

1117
02:16:13,370 --> 02:16:16,830
...to spend that one day with, you
are willing to die a thousand deaths

1118
02:16:19,540 --> 02:16:20,510
Who is it, Akash?

1119
02:17:57,910 --> 02:17:59,210
No so easily!

1120
02:18:00,740 --> 02:18:03,040
You still haven't told me
who you saw

1121
02:18:05,750 --> 02:18:07,220
You seem quite sure that I
saw someone?

1122
02:18:07,920 --> 02:18:09,720
Yes. Because today for
the first time...

1123
02:18:09,920 --> 02:18:12,220
...you're talking less
and thinking more!

1124
02:18:24,170 --> 02:18:24,790
Then listen

1125
02:18:27,170 --> 02:18:27,800
I saw her...

1126
02:18:30,170 --> 02:18:30,800
And I felt...

1127
02:18:31,010 --> 02:18:33,640
...perhaps this is what
they call love

1128
02:18:41,180 --> 02:18:42,310
I wanted to touch her...

1129
02:18:44,690 --> 02:18:45,990
...hold her in my arms...

1130
02:18:49,190 --> 02:18:51,990
I saw such innocence
in her eyes...

1131
02:18:54,860 --> 02:18:55,990
...like I see in your eyes now

1132
02:19:00,700 --> 02:19:01,830
Her voice...

1133
02:19:02,210 --> 02:19:03,830
...had the kind of magic
your voice has

1134
02:19:06,040 --> 02:19:09,840
I can still feel the fragrance
of her breath...

1135
02:19:10,050 --> 02:19:11,510
...like I can feel
in your breath now

1136
02:19:13,680 --> 02:19:14,480
Who was she?

1137
02:19:25,900 --> 02:19:27,020
That fat opera singer!

1138
02:19:45,080 --> 02:19:51,380
Shalini, come inside... at once!

1139
02:20:45,980 --> 02:20:47,600
I think the two of you should
talk alone

1140
02:20:57,090 --> 02:20:59,560
Where had you gone?
- To the opera

1141
02:21:01,820 --> 02:21:02,620
With Akash!

1142
02:21:04,490 --> 02:21:06,790
How many times have I told you
not to meet him!

1143
02:21:10,170 --> 02:21:13,470
Rohit, will you keep telling me
all my life...

1144
02:21:13,670 --> 02:21:15,140
...who I should or should not meet!

1145
02:21:18,510 --> 02:21:19,130
Yes. I will

1146
02:21:19,840 --> 02:21:23,140
And you will never see Akash
again. You got that?

1147
02:21:29,690 --> 02:21:32,810
Rohit, I need some time to think
and you need it too

1148
02:22:53,410 --> 02:22:56,700
Shalini had called.
She said it's important

1149
02:23:09,090 --> 02:23:10,890
Hi, Rohit. It's Akash

1150
02:23:12,420 --> 02:23:14,720
Is Shalini there? She had called

1151
02:23:15,260 --> 02:23:19,060
I know. We are going back...
to get married

1152
02:23:24,770 --> 02:23:25,740
Can I speak to Shalini?

1153
02:23:53,700 --> 02:23:55,170
That's good news

1154
02:23:57,800 --> 02:23:59,430
Akash, we are going back tomorrow

1155
02:24:00,810 --> 02:24:02,270
Can you come for dinner tonight?

1156
02:24:05,310 --> 02:24:07,440
I don't know. Bye

1157
02:24:24,830 --> 02:24:25,960
Hey, Akash! We thought you
weren't going to make it

1158
02:25:08,640 --> 02:25:11,010
They're beautiful. Thanks

1159
02:25:12,710 --> 02:25:13,400
What will you drink?

1160
02:25:15,150 --> 02:25:18,410
We can drink later. Let's eat first.
I'm starving

1161
02:25:45,410 --> 02:25:48,210
Shalini, have you told
Mahesh Uncle...

1162
02:25:48,410 --> 02:25:49,880
...how you and Akash met?

1163
02:25:53,920 --> 02:25:54,440
No?

1164
02:25:57,220 --> 02:25:58,380
Really, Mahesh Uncle...

1165
02:25:58,960 --> 02:26:01,220
I don't know what you'd have
done if you were there

1166
02:26:01,430 --> 02:26:02,550
What happened?

1167
02:26:04,360 --> 02:26:06,060
It was at my graduation
party

1168
02:26:06,730 --> 02:26:07,390
Shalini was with me

1169
02:26:07,600 --> 02:26:09,660
Perhaps Akash didn't know
that...

1170
02:26:19,940 --> 02:26:21,240
Sorry for the punch

1171
02:26:24,620 --> 02:26:27,080
No, Rohit. It was my fault

1172
02:26:30,120 --> 02:26:33,090
But to tell you the truth,
I think I was lucky

1173
02:26:34,430 --> 02:26:34,910
What do you mean?

1174
02:26:35,260 --> 02:26:38,820
I mean, if Shalini was with me...

1175
02:26:39,800 --> 02:26:41,930
...and someone had acted fresh...

1176
02:26:43,640 --> 02:26:44,930
I'd have killed him

1177
02:26:58,450 --> 02:26:58,940
That is...

1178
02:27:00,290 --> 02:27:01,780
If Shalini was with you

1179
02:27:34,690 --> 02:27:35,280
Hey, wait...

1180
02:27:56,270 --> 02:27:58,830
You're coming to our wedding,
aren't you?

1181
02:27:59,880 --> 02:28:02,680
No, I can't make it. There's a lot
of work to be done

1182
02:28:05,020 --> 02:28:06,010
Some friend you are!

1183
02:28:07,620 --> 02:28:10,180
Anyway, don't forget to call us to
your wedding

1184
02:28:11,020 --> 02:28:11,850
We'll definitely be there

1185
02:28:12,760 --> 02:28:14,520
I'm not going to get married

1186
02:28:15,260 --> 02:28:15,850
Why?

1187
02:28:18,300 --> 02:28:20,860
It's necessary to love someone
to get married

1188
02:28:21,730 --> 02:28:23,200
And I believe...

1189
02:28:23,570 --> 02:28:25,370
...this thing called love doesn't
exist in the world

1190
02:28:27,970 --> 02:28:29,670
Shalini and I love each other

1191
02:28:29,910 --> 02:28:31,710
That's why we're getting married.
Isn't that so, Shalini?

1192
02:28:35,080 --> 02:28:39,710
You both shouldn't ask each other
this question. Ask yourself

1193
02:28:45,760 --> 02:28:46,550
I better go

1194
02:29:19,560 --> 02:29:21,750
You left your jacket with me
the other night

1195
02:29:35,640 --> 02:29:40,600
Some day I want to tell you why
I am marrying Rohit

1196
02:29:40,810 --> 02:29:44,770
Why? What's the need to tell me?

1197
02:29:47,450 --> 02:29:48,280
I need to...

1198
02:29:49,620 --> 02:29:51,280
Because we both know...

1199
02:29:54,390 --> 02:29:56,290
...that night at the opera,
when you shut your eyes...

1200
02:29:57,630 --> 02:30:00,120
...it wasn't the fat opera singer
you saw

1201
02:30:26,530 --> 02:30:33,160
Loneliness

1202
02:30:36,300 --> 02:30:40,670
This Ioneliness...

1203
02:30:46,150 --> 02:30:50,850
Why have I stumbled on
the path of love

1204
02:30:51,150 --> 02:30:55,680
All my dreams lie shattered
A sense of gloom lies heavy

1205
02:30:55,890 --> 02:31:00,350
Every joy is be numbed

1206
02:31:00,730 --> 02:31:05,790
My very life is lost

1207
02:31:06,070 --> 02:31:10,770
I am being punished
for loving you

1208
02:31:10,970 --> 02:31:15,840
Loneliness...

1209
02:31:16,280 --> 02:31:20,580
Loneliness stretches over
miles and miles

1210
02:32:10,130 --> 02:32:15,590
In my dream I saw
a hand in my hand

1211
02:32:20,140 --> 02:32:25,770
Now I am blinded by the
shards of a shattered dream

1212
02:32:39,990 --> 02:32:44,450
Someone was here yesterday

1213
02:32:44,670 --> 02:32:49,760
but today there is no one

1214
02:32:50,170 --> 02:32:54,970
Like a cobra's venomous hiss
it envelopes my very breath...

1215
02:32:55,180 --> 02:32:59,840
...this Ioneliness

1216
02:33:00,220 --> 02:33:04,410
has brought tears to my eyes

1217
02:33:54,400 --> 02:33:59,860
Oh how could my hope for
something be so futile

1218
02:34:04,340 --> 02:34:10,150
I've embarked on a journey
to which there is no destination

1219
02:34:23,930 --> 02:34:28,230
Where should I go?

1220
02:34:28,600 --> 02:34:33,700
To whom shall I explain?

1221
02:34:34,140 --> 02:34:36,230
What I had wanted...

1222
02:34:36,440 --> 02:34:38,740
And why I ended up with...

1223
02:34:38,950 --> 02:34:43,910
...this Ioneliness

1224
02:34:44,120 --> 02:34:48,250
Loneliness
deeply dark as the night

1225
02:34:58,770 --> 02:35:03,600
Why have I stumbled on
the path of love

1226
02:35:03,800 --> 02:35:08,240
All my dreams lie shattered
A sense of gloom lies heavy

1227
02:35:08,440 --> 02:35:13,110
Every joy is be numbed

1228
02:35:13,310 --> 02:35:18,620
My very life is lost

1229
02:35:18,920 --> 02:35:23,450
I am being punished
for loving you

1230
02:35:23,660 --> 02:35:28,320
Loneliness...

1231
02:35:28,830 --> 02:35:33,130
Loneliness stretches over
miles and miles

1232
02:36:20,380 --> 02:36:21,610
Hello, Aunty. Is Sameer home?

1233
02:36:21,950 --> 02:36:22,680
Who is this?

1234
02:36:26,590 --> 02:36:29,520
You want to talk to Sameer
and you've called Siddharth!

1235
02:36:30,590 --> 02:36:31,350
How are you?

1236
02:36:32,030 --> 02:36:33,860
I... I'm okay, Aunty

1237
02:36:34,460 --> 02:36:38,360
He's gone to Kasauli. Give me
your number. I'll give it to him

1238
02:36:40,030 --> 02:36:42,030
No, it's okay.
I'll call him

1239
02:37:36,090 --> 02:37:36,850
How are you, son?

1240
02:37:40,890 --> 02:37:41,550
I'm okay, Dad

1241
02:37:44,030 --> 02:37:47,330
What's wrong? Are you unwell?

1242
02:37:48,670 --> 02:37:49,690
No, it's nothing like that

1243
02:37:51,110 --> 02:37:52,440
Been working all day...

1244
02:37:52,810 --> 02:37:53,600
I'm tired, that's all

1245
02:38:05,920 --> 02:38:07,550
Come back home, Akash

1246
02:38:36,380 --> 02:38:37,320
What's wrong, Akash?

1247
02:38:39,590 --> 02:38:41,490
I've never seen you like this
before

1248
02:38:42,690 --> 02:38:43,750
I'm in love, Dad

1249
02:38:46,930 --> 02:38:49,620
So what's the problem?

1250
02:38:51,160 --> 02:38:52,650
She is marrying somebody else

1251
02:38:56,870 --> 02:38:59,340
Have you told her you love her?

1252
02:39:01,480 --> 02:39:01,960
No

1253
02:39:03,480 --> 02:39:04,910
Does she love you?

1254
02:39:09,350 --> 02:39:10,110
Yes, she does

1255
02:39:12,860 --> 02:39:13,980
Has she told you?

1256
02:39:20,200 --> 02:39:24,690
Akash, you must tell her
how you feel

1257
02:39:27,340 --> 02:39:27,800
No

1258
02:39:28,610 --> 02:39:29,200
Why not?

1259
02:39:32,610 --> 02:39:34,040
She is marrying somebody else

1260
02:39:38,080 --> 02:39:42,380
There are many things in this world
that are beyond our understanding

1261
02:39:43,550 --> 02:39:45,380
When a person decides something...

1262
02:39:46,590 --> 02:39:49,720
...there must be a reason for that
decision

1263
02:39:50,860 --> 02:39:56,090
You say that the girl loves you
but is marrying someone else

1264
02:39:57,430 --> 02:40:01,730
Have you tried to find out
why she's doing it?

1265
02:40:04,210 --> 02:40:06,300
What's the reason for her decision?

1266
02:40:25,490 --> 02:40:26,430
How's Shalini?

1267
02:40:28,260 --> 02:40:28,990
She isn't happy

1268
02:40:31,130 --> 02:40:32,100
And how could she be?

1269
02:40:33,270 --> 02:40:36,240
She is marrying Rohit
but loves you

1270
02:40:40,410 --> 02:40:42,070
Did she tell you that?
- No

1271
02:40:44,410 --> 02:40:46,140
Did you ever tell me you love her?

1272
02:40:51,620 --> 02:40:53,380
Then why's she getting married?

1273
02:40:56,190 --> 02:40:58,680
Rohit's father and Shalini's father
were business partners

1274
02:41:01,000 --> 02:41:05,930
Shalini was six when her parents
were killed in a car accident

1275
02:41:07,640 --> 02:41:12,540
I was her only relative but
I wasn't able to support her

1276
02:41:15,640 --> 02:41:16,870
Rohit's parents took her in...

1277
02:41:17,080 --> 02:41:17,640
...not only into their home

1278
02:41:17,850 --> 02:41:19,780
but their hearts and their life

1279
02:41:21,050 --> 02:41:22,540
They've done a lot for her

1280
02:41:23,650 --> 02:41:27,650
If they want her to marry Rohit,
Shalini can't refuse

1281
02:41:30,190 --> 02:41:31,420
What else can she do?

1282
02:41:33,200 --> 02:41:36,760
On one hand are the people who've
given her the life she's living

1283
02:41:38,270 --> 02:41:39,200
On the other hand is a man...

1284
02:41:39,400 --> 02:41:42,100
She doesn't even know if he loves
her or not

1285
02:41:43,270 --> 02:41:47,940
Akash, what are you doing man!
Go and tell her you love her

1286
02:41:51,610 --> 02:41:53,580
Akash, only you know what
you have to do

1287
02:41:55,080 --> 02:41:57,210
Just know this. Tonight is
the Sangeet function...

1288
02:41:58,550 --> 02:41:59,750
...and tomorrow the wedding

1289
02:42:02,030 --> 02:42:04,890
Whatever your decision,
you must make it today

1290
02:44:19,790 --> 02:44:20,850
Will you marry me?

1291
02:44:30,340 --> 02:44:32,970
Not even if I tell you that
I love you?

1292
02:45:14,380 --> 02:45:14,940
Shalini...

1293
02:45:16,950 --> 02:45:19,010
I love you and only you

1294
02:45:21,560 --> 02:45:22,580
My every breath...

1295
02:45:24,260 --> 02:45:25,350
...every heartbeat...

1296
02:45:27,130 --> 02:45:29,720
...every moment,
is for you, Shalini

1297
02:45:32,570 --> 02:45:37,730
I'm sure that I was born
so that I could love you

1298
02:45:39,240 --> 02:45:41,870
And you were born to become mine

1299
02:45:43,180 --> 02:45:44,540
You are mine, Shalini

1300
02:45:45,610 --> 02:45:47,380
And if you ask your heart...

1301
02:45:48,520 --> 02:45:51,610
...you will know that I speak
the truth

1302
02:45:58,590 --> 02:46:01,220
What's going on! Who is this boy?

1303
02:46:01,600 --> 02:46:02,390
I'll tell you

1304
02:46:03,600 --> 02:46:07,300
He is Akash Malhotra,
A.K. Malhotra's son...

1305
02:46:07,970 --> 02:46:10,230
...who's been after Shalini,
wagging his tail

1306
02:46:11,210 --> 02:46:14,900
I hit him once but I guess
it wasn't enough, huh?

1307
02:46:15,980 --> 02:46:17,100
I won't leave you today!

1308
02:46:17,310 --> 02:46:22,550
You will do no such thing, Rohit.
I want to speak to Shalini first

1309
02:46:51,850 --> 02:46:54,610
No, Rohit! You wait here.
- But Dad! This is my life...

1310
02:48:13,400 --> 02:48:17,060
Mahesh, I feel very hurt today

1311
02:48:18,240 --> 02:48:20,930
I always thought that Shalini was
my daughter

1312
02:48:21,840 --> 02:48:24,870
But today I feel that she has
never thought of us as her own

1313
02:48:27,110 --> 02:48:30,010
She wants to repay her debt to us
by marrying Rohit

1314
02:48:32,550 --> 02:48:33,040
All right

1315
02:48:36,420 --> 02:48:39,450
Shalini, you must repay us

1316
02:48:41,190 --> 02:48:44,890
For looking after you from
childhood till now... you owe us

1317
02:48:45,730 --> 02:48:48,560
For giving you whatever you
asked for... you owe us

1318
02:48:49,830 --> 02:48:52,770
For shielding you from
even a hint of trouble...

1319
02:48:52,870 --> 02:48:53,700
...you owe us

1320
02:48:55,770 --> 02:48:59,940
Now if you want to repay all that
you owe us... see us happy...

1321
02:49:02,910 --> 02:49:04,440
Then marry Akash

1322
02:49:11,260 --> 02:49:12,780
Can you do this much for me?

1323
02:49:32,940 --> 02:49:33,570
Come...

1324
02:49:44,920 --> 02:49:49,020
Take care of her.
She is my daughter

1325
02:50:24,560 --> 02:50:25,320
Just a minute, Dad

1326
02:50:27,700 --> 02:50:30,460
You can't do this! Mom, why
aren't you saying anything?

1327
02:50:31,100 --> 02:50:33,000
Let her go, Rohit

1328
02:50:36,310 --> 02:50:39,500
You care about Shalini's happiness
but don't give a damn about mine!

1329
02:50:39,810 --> 02:50:44,270
Rohit, if Shalini is not happy
being with you...

1330
02:50:44,920 --> 02:50:46,410
...how can you ever be happy?

1331
02:50:48,550 --> 02:50:49,710
This can't happen to me!

1332
02:50:53,460 --> 02:50:54,620
I won't allow this!

1333
02:50:58,030 --> 02:50:58,520
What are you doing?

1334
02:51:33,900 --> 02:51:35,520
I love Akash

1335
02:51:56,590 --> 02:51:57,820
All his life he said...

1336
02:51:58,120 --> 02:51:59,820
I won't say "I love you" to anyone

1337
02:52:00,260 --> 02:52:01,250
And when he had to say it...

1338
02:52:01,590 --> 02:52:04,460
It was at someone's wedding
in front of 300 people!

1339
02:52:08,770 --> 02:52:09,820
Did you call him?

1340
02:52:13,640 --> 02:52:14,470
What did he say?

1341
02:52:17,510 --> 02:52:18,500
He wasn't home

1342
02:52:24,180 --> 02:52:25,910
I told you he won't come

1343
02:54:19,300 --> 02:54:21,290
Can I talk to Sid?

1344
02:54:42,650 --> 02:54:43,420
How are you?

1345
02:54:45,220 --> 02:54:47,020
Fine. How are you?

1346
02:54:53,730 --> 02:54:54,890
Forgive me

1347
02:54:57,840 --> 02:54:59,360
I must apologise too

1348
02:55:00,600 --> 02:55:04,440
Some other time.
It's my turn today

1349
02:55:06,910 --> 02:55:08,170
You haven't changed
at all

1350
02:55:09,010 --> 02:55:12,950
Ya. Anyway, it's hard to improve
on perfection

1351
02:55:19,260 --> 02:55:20,620
Where are you? When can we meet?

1352
02:55:22,090 --> 02:55:25,690
Today. Now. This very moment

1353
02:57:04,030 --> 02:57:08,160
Now... there's no pain...
nor any fear

1354
02:57:12,640 --> 02:57:14,130
I feel good

1355
02:57:16,540 --> 02:57:17,530
It's peaceful here

1356
02:57:22,150 --> 02:57:24,280
You're a good boy, Siddharth

1357
02:57:28,320 --> 02:57:30,020
You always stood by me

1358
02:57:34,690 --> 02:57:36,350
You want me to be happy,
don't you...

1359
02:57:40,270 --> 02:57:41,430
Then... you be happy

1360
02:57:44,270 --> 02:57:45,030
You will, won't you?

1361
02:57:45,410 --> 02:57:45,960
I will

1362
02:57:56,920 --> 02:57:58,350
Life is so strange

1363
02:58:00,590 --> 02:58:01,990
Some relationships...

1364
02:58:05,190 --> 02:58:06,820
...don't have any name

1365
02:58:13,630 --> 02:58:15,660
You and I will always...

1366
03:00:12,520 --> 03:00:15,210
Hey Sid, look at your ship

1367
03:00:16,520 --> 03:00:19,010
It was so small 2 years ago.
Look how much it's grown

1368
03:00:22,300 --> 03:00:25,290
If you guys wanted to be by
yourselves, you should've told us

1369
03:00:28,530 --> 03:00:31,260
See! I'm getting told off because
of you

1370
03:00:31,470 --> 03:00:32,460
I've been telling you, let's go

1371
03:00:32,740 --> 03:00:33,230
What?

1372
03:00:33,910 --> 03:00:34,800
Come on

1373
03:01:03,100 --> 03:01:03,900
Come on man